    "body": "You can do this if you really want it aggregate non-numeric types\n\ncurrenly you cannot pass this flag to the groupby `sum` (which is a wrapper around a cython function), but could be changed to do so.\n\n```\nIn [5]: df.groupby(df[\"B\"]).apply(lambda x: x.sum(numeric_only=False))\nOut[5]: \n      A  B\nB         \n1   4.0  3\n2  13.5  6\n\n[2 rows x 2 columns]\n\n```\n\nI don't think this is a very useful case, so going to close this. If you could like to do a PR or thing this should really be included could include on a future version. (so reopen and comment in that case).\n"
