    "body": "What was misleading (ie bitten by the bug) is that the column \"A\" sometimes disappeared from the groupby(...).sum(...) and sometimes not (depending on whether the data had a mixed type or not).\nThe flag numeric_only=False may be a better default for the DataFrameGroupBy.sum() operator.\nLike it is apparently for the DataFrame.sum() as  df.sum() gives\n\n```\nA    8.5\nB    5.0\ndtype: float64\n```\n\nEven stranger:\n\n```\nprint DataFrameGroupBy.sum(df.groupby(df[\"B\"]))\nprint DataFrameGroupBy.sum(df.groupby([\"B\"]))\n\n   B\nB   \n1  3\n2  2\n\n[2 rows x 1 columns]\n     A\nB     \n1  4.0\n2  4.5\n\n[2 rows x 1 columns]\n```\n\nso it looks the numeric_only flag is set differently in function of the paths... \nIs it worth fixing for consistency ?\n"
  },
