    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I went through the tests in test_groupby and saw 5 tests failing when changing the default behavior of DataFrameGroupBy.sum(). \nEssentially, the tests use the following properties:\n- the dataframe is pruned from any column with mixed dtypes data when using .sum() (as the default for numeric_only=True)\n- the .sum() keeps the dtype of the column if it is numeric, e.g. int64 stays int64 when summed (when using numeric_only=False, data can be casted to float64).\n\nSo the behavior change may impact more people indirectly... What do you think ?\n\nTo make the flag to be passed in looks simple. The lines 96/98 of groupby.py should go from\n\n```\ndef _groupby_function(name, alias, npfunc, numeric_only=True,\n                      _convert=False):\n    def f(self):\n```\n\nto\n\n```\ndef _groupby_function(name, alias, npfunc, numeric_only=True,\n                      _convert=False):\n    def f(self, numeric_only=numeric_only):\n```\n"
  },
